						<summary>

						<p>Slab standing at 'Kūsaḷabeṭṭu' in the hamlet Kirāḍi.</p>						

						<p>Bukka I, 1370 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged record seems to register a gift of money income and also land for the supply of flower-garlands and other service, to god Kōṭinātha (Kōṭīśvara)dēva. <hi rend="bold">Gōparasa</hi> is stated to have been administering <hi rend="bold">Bārakūru-rājya</hi> at the instance of the king. Other details are lost.</p>						

						<p>It is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka [1293], Sādhāraṇa, Pushya śu. 1 • • •, Saṁkramaṇa.</hi> In the given cyclic year Saṁkramaṇa, i.e., Uttarāyaṇa-saṁkramaṇa, occurred on <hi rend="bold">1370 A.D., December 27, Friday</hi> when the <hi rend="italic">tithi</hi> was śu. 9 in the month of Pushya. This might be the intended date. The Śaka year was current.</p>						

						</summary>
